### Summary

Issue #494 is mostly done — RPM was raised from 10 to 30, per-user JWT buckets are in place, and upstream retry logic exists. The one remaining gap: the frontend has no 429-specific handling. When rate-limited, users see the generic "Error communicating with server." message instead of a clear, actionable notice.

